1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,000
Your phone after 10 PM
is borrowing energy from tomorrow.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:08,000
You scroll for "just 5 minutes." That turns
into 45 minutes. Your brain thinks it's daytime.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Blue light after dark suppresses melatonin for up to 90 minutes. That means
even if you sleep at 11, your body doesn't start recovering until 12:30.

4
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Set a phone alarm for 60 minutes before your
target bedtime. When it rings: phone goes face-down.

5
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:30,000
VOLT Sleep sends you a wind-down
reminder. Free. Link in bio.

